Russians warned about fake calls from banks
In Russia, the number of calls from scammers who replace the bank&#39;s phone number has increased.
It is reported by &quot;Kommersant&quot; with reference to the data of the Central Bank.
In the summer of 2019, the regulator handed over to telecom operators information about more than 2.5 thousand numbers from which customers of various financial institutions called.
In 189 cases, operators detected a number change.
Another 218 numbers were blocked, and in 59 cases restrictions were placed on the use of financial services.
Artem Sychev, deputy head of the information security department of the Central Bank, said that a wide range of Russian banks faced the substitution of the number.
He explained that operators do not always respond to warnings from the Central Bank about fraudulent calls, citing the absence of such a duty in the Law on Communications.
Otkritie Bank, Rosbank and Alfa-Bank confirmed information about an increase in the number of fraudulent calls with a number substitution.
According to the Beeline press service, some of the information about fraudulent calls that the Central Bank transmitted was incorrect: the lists included numbers that are actually used by banks to communicate with customers.
Their blocking would lead to disruptions in the work of the organization.
Artem Sychev said that the Central Bank plans to create a database of scam numbers, which the telecom operator will contact with each call to verify the number.
He explained that in order to create such a base, amendments to the legislation would be required.
